<P><PB N="130" REF="179">
After &vers; 172. in the MS.</P>
<Q><L>Say, what rewards this idle world imparts,</L>
<L>Or fit for &s;earching heads or hone&s;t hearts.</L></Q>
<P><PB N="133" REF="182" MS="Y">
VER. 207. <HI>Boa&s;t the pure blood</HI> &amp;c.] in the MS. thus,</P>
<LG>
<L>The riche&s;t blood, right-honourably old,</L>
<L>Down from Lucretia to Lucretia roll'd,</L>
<L>May &s;well thy heart and gallop in thy brea&s;t,</L>
